&ldquo;I&rsquo;m glad you see it that way,&rdquo; she whispered. &ldquo;After all, these are my personal powers.&rdquo;
James eyes widened. He knew about those - Amanda&rsquo;s heat vision, Ms. Riley&rsquo;s ability to create permanent clothes, Ms. Harland’s mind control, Deziree&rsquo;s invisibility and Miu&rsquo;s super radar ability - but none could hold a candle against Michelle&hellip; at least not for him.
Even though they were staring into each other&rsquo;s eyes, he could practically feel her smile grow brighter as he came to that conclusion. After all, from what they had learned, these powers seemed to be at least partially affected by the user&rsquo;s personality. Simply put, the fact that he loved Michelle&rsquo;s personal powers more than any other was a subtle sign that he loved her as well. Not that he needed that hint.
&ldquo;If you like it that much, how about I show you even more? So far I only gave you small glimpses of what I&rsquo;ve done until now, and in my depowered state no less. Wanna see how Amanda&rsquo;s second transformation looked in slow motion? I think I could even make it easier for you to understand this.&rdquo;
&ldquo;How would that work?&rdquo; James almost expected her to suggest drinking the potion to solve that issue.
&ldquo;Of course not. For some reason, I made a link to the plant that gave me these powers. Even though it doesn&rsquo;t have any brain or intelligence of it&rsquo;s own, I could share part of my brain for it to use. If I do the same with you, you should be able to perceive things the same way I did without getting a headache.&rdquo;
&ldquo;You never cease to amaze me. I probably won&rsquo;t get such a detailed view on a transformation of yours, would I?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Not a third person view, no. At least not without the same kind of powers. But I could share with you the detailed memory of how it felt to me. Last time I only gave you a rough version.&rdquo;
&ldquo;You really wanna do this do you? Shouldn&rsquo;t we talk about our little disagreement first? &quot;
&ldquo;Correct me if I&rsquo;m wrong, but your main issue with taking the potion and becoming super is that you&rsquo;d settle with me, and feel that we don&rsquo;t know each other enough for that kind of commitment. Through our bond, I already know you a lot better than I should after such a short time, but it seems like you don&rsquo;t know me as well. Apparently the bond works better for me, so it&rsquo;s only fair to let you catch up.&rdquo;
James couldn&rsquo;t argue with that. She was right. If she really could read him like that all the time, then she would know him a lot better than he did her. Balancing things out would be the only plausible solution, no matter how he looked at it.
&ldquo;Alright, you&rsquo;ve got a point there.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Good. Then let&rsquo;s lie down for this; I&rsquo;ll need my whole concentration.&rdquo;
He didn&rsquo;t need to be asked twice. Not a minute later, they were lying in his bed, her on top of him, partially floating, her eyes glowing bright before&hellip;.
James suddenly found himself standing in a white space. Michelle hovered naked in front of him and he noticed that he was naked as well.
&ldquo;What is this?&rdquo; He thought it to himself, but found his mouth asking the question out loud.
&ldquo;Some kind of mental meeting place,&rdquo; Michelle answered. &ldquo;I used it to talk to the plant, but it took me a while to realize just who I was really talking to. Anyway, this space enables me to share my memories in the most effective way. Is there anything you would like to see first?&rdquo;
&ldquo;I don&rsquo;t know, actually. There are so many things I want to know about you that I can&rsquo;t decide where to start. Maybe you could decide where to start?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Alright, then; how about I start small and show you how I found the seed that changed my life?&rdquo;
He nodded and the white space disappeared, to be replaced by the streets of the city. Somewhere downtown; a usual place for Michelle to go on a walk. James noticed that the images were blurry at times, especially the faces of the people walking around. That was only logical considering this was Michelle&rsquo;s memory from three months ago. While she had a clear knowledge about the buildings here, she had not paid too much attention to the people around her. Except&hellip;
One man going in the opposite direction stuck out. Unlike the others, he was clearly visible, meaning that Michelle had bothered remembering him. A sudden wave of animosity came over him and as he wondered whether he was getting jealous of this guy, he noticed that this was actually part of Michelle&rsquo;s memory.
They passed each other, and past Michelle gave him an aside-glance. “At least pretend to recognize me, asshole!”&hellip; James could hear her thoughts from back then clearly. Unfortunately her attention would have been better spent on the pavement, as she suddenly slipped and fell on her back.
&ldquo;Ouch,&rdquo; he heard Michelle exclaim as she landed. The people around her, commenting her misfortune with a slight laugh, but generally not paying her too much mind. The man however, turned around and laughed wholeheartedly.
&ldquo;You better watch your step,&rdquo; he joked before a loud growl made him grab his stomach.
&ldquo;&hellip; And you better watch your food,&rdquo; Michelle countered. &ldquo;Apparently your last meal was from before the evacuation.&rdquo;
With gritted teeth the man turned around, and with hasty steps was probably about to find the next bathroom. James felt Michelle&rsquo;s mood lighten.&ldquo;Well, there really is a God,&rdquo; he heard her think before she noticed just what she had tripped over. Before her lay a small, brown almond-shaped object. Michelle picked it up and figured it must be some kind of seed. Given that this was the first day after the evacuation ended, Michelle decided just then and there to plant it as a memento of that day. Just to see what kind of plant it was.
The white space returned, as the memory was over now.
&ldquo;The rest is easily explained, I planted the seed, it grew into the plant you&rsquo;ve seen at my nightstand, and it produced a liquid that turned me into this.&rdquo;
&ldquo;What about the man you met there? You seemed to hate him.&rdquo;
Michelle averted her gaze.
&ldquo;Let me guess, he was an ex-boyfriend of yours.&rdquo; James said.
The blonde amazon shook her head. &ldquo;That would be giving him far too much credit. He was just a one-night stand. And it was my own mistake to believe we would be more than that.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Sorry to hear that,&rdquo; James walked over to hug her.
&ldquo;It&rsquo;s okay. He was an episode of the past, but you are the present.&rdquo; Michelle blushed as she added, &ldquo;And the future.&rdquo;
&ldquo;You wanted me to get to know you better, how about you show me how it went with him?&rdquo;
Michelle&rsquo;s eyes widened, yet her blush didn&rsquo;t disappear. &ldquo;Y-you sure about that? That wasn&rsquo;t exactly a good episode of my life.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Which is exactly why I want to see it,&rdquo; James answered. &ldquo;You already gave me glimpses of your heroic deeds, showing how great you can be. But for us to work as a couple, I will also have to know your bad sides, and who knows? Maybe I like what you consider these bad sides?&rdquo;
Michelle gulped, but nodded. &ldquo;That would be great. OK, I&rsquo;ll show you.&rdquo;
And so she did. For the next few hours Michelle did nothing but show James episodes of her life. True to her word she gave him full disclosure, a leap of faith that dwarfed everything she had done so far.
The night at the hospital felt a lot less lonely than the day for Fred. The news that his sister had died had been more of a shock than he had expected. He thought he had been mentally prepared for this to happen. That Amanda had been digging in this very wound hadn&rsquo;t helped there, especially due to the changes she had gone through these last few days. On the other hand, the very fact that she was still there for him had kept him sane for now. After all, the reason Erika died even before her time was that she, for a short time, had the same kind of powers as Amanda had.
At least that&rsquo;s what Amanda had told him earlier today, when everything had become clearer – yet so much more complicated. Now they were engaged, something he hadn&rsquo;t even dreamed possible. His problems hadn&rsquo;t decreased: he still had a ruined knee and a heart that would fail in a few years. Still, it felt comforting that Amanda knew about that now. When she had exclaimed that they would solve these problems, he had believed her. Had it been because of her new powers? Of these abilities that defied explanation?
Fred felt compelled to look outside – and wasn&rsquo;t surprised as he saw a figure just outside the window, a woman with a long red mane and glowing orange eyes opening the window from the outside. What surprised him was that Amanda&rsquo;s outfit was a lot more casual than her last one when she had come here in her super form. Not that he was complaining about the tight jeans and the sexy top, but he remembered her mentioning that her ability to create clothes wouldn&rsquo;t allow an outfit like that.
&ldquo;It&rsquo;s been a present of sorts,&rdquo; Amanda whispered as if to answer his thoughts directly.
&ldquo;From who?&rdquo;
Amanda&rsquo;s face darkened a bit. &ldquo;Erika,&rdquo; she whispered again. &ldquo;This was her individual power that she passed on to me. Remember when I told you about the little fight we had because she didn&rsquo;t know it was me? She gave me some of her energy and apparently a boost for the whole clothes creation ability.&rdquo;
&ldquo;You are full of surprises,&rdquo; Fred exclaimed.
&ldquo;And I haven&rsquo;t even started yet,&rdquo; Amanda giggled, placing her hand on his knee.
Fred expected the pain to instantly go away – like always when Amanda did that. But this time she seemed to be trying something different. Instead of disappearing, the pain actually got worse – and he could see the strain on her face.
After about a minute, she gasped and stopped whatever she was trying. &ldquo;Alright… the whole healing power part&hellip; will take a bit longer. But it looks like I made some progress on that front. If I can keep it up, you&rsquo;ll be walking by the weekend.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I wouldn&rsquo;t believe it if it weren&rsquo;t you saying that.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Aww,&rdquo; Amanda leaned in for a kiss, which he gladly returned. &ldquo;Like I said, I have some news for you. There&rsquo;s good news, bad news, and important news. Which one would you like to hear first?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s start with bad news. I have a feeling it won&rsquo;t be the worst news I hear today.&rdquo;
&ldquo;You may be right. Still, the fact that Susan Harland became super too is definitely bad news.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Please tell me you are kidding.&rdquo;
Amanda shook her head. &ldquo;Which bring me to the good news: Michelle took care of her.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Michelle? Oh I get it: she&rsquo;s the one who saved Erika back then&hellip; shouldn&rsquo;t you have tried to keep that to yourself?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Nope. She told her boyfriend about me, so why shouldn&rsquo;t I tell my fiancé? Don&rsquo;t worry, she&rsquo;ll be fine with you knowing.&rdquo;
Fred rolled his eyes. &ldquo;Of course she will! She&rsquo;s way too trusting at times. Remember that one guy she hooked up with thinking it was her soulmate? Didn&rsquo;t go beyond a one-night stand, if I remember correctly.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Would you rather have her be bitter and disillusioned about it? Sure, she&rsquo;s been quite trusting and leaves herself wide open at times. But the way she&rsquo;s willing to believe in people is what makes her so good at helping them.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Can&rsquo;t argue with that.&rdquo; Actually Fred didn&rsquo;t know Michelle well enough to actually argue at all. &ldquo;I just hope she&rsquo;s not in over her head. If these superpowers are popping up that frequently, it would be best if the poster girl remained one of the good guys.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Don&rsquo;t worry, if worse comes to worse, I&rsquo;ll talk some sense into her,&rdquo; Amanda exclaimed as she slid under the blanket. Her clothes dissolved into thin air, leaving her in only a bra and panties. They kissed again, slowly.
&ldquo;So what is the important news?&rdquo; Fred asked. He knew he was rushing things here, but, with her so close, his rational mind was eager to take a vacation.
&ldquo;Well, you did hear that these powers come with a significant mutation that basically turns me half-alien, right?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Yeah,&rdquo; he nodded. That train of thought made it easier for him to remain focused, though.
&ldquo;As you can probably imagine, the different number of chromosomes makes it pretty much impossible to reproduce&hellip;&rdquo;
Fred gulped. &ldquo;I-if you want to tell me that you can&rsquo;t have children, then it&rsquo;s okay. All I remember about my parents is that they died far too early, and that both Erika and I had inherited their condition. I don&rsquo;t really like the idea that my kids would suffer a similar fate, so it wasn&rsquo;t really high on my agenda to have any.&rdquo;
Amanda&rsquo;s face darkened – due to her eyes not glowing as bright anymore. &ldquo;Well, I fully intend to fix that little condition of yours. And actually, you turning into a half-alien hybrid like myself would be part of my agenda, too.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Wouldn&rsquo;t I die just like Erika?&rdquo;
&ldquo;I&rsquo;m still trying to figure out a way to prevent that. So far the best lead would be Susan. Apparently she didn&rsquo;t transform back to normal after she was out of power. That could be the key to saving you.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I see. I don’t know too much about these powers of yours, so I&rsquo;ll trust you on that. If you think you found a way to cure me, I&rsquo;ll go along with it. Even if it means to go down the road that killed my sister.&rdquo;
&ldquo;And the becoming half-alien part wouldn&rsquo;t bother you?&rdquo;
&ldquo;You still look and act pretty human, so it can&rsquo;t be that bad. Besides, if this really cures me, then this would apply to any children of ours too, right? In that case we could really start a family!&rdquo;
Amanda simply smiled at him, her eyes shining bright again, maybe even brighter than they did originally. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m glad you see it that way.&rdquo; She then picked his hand and placed it on her belly. &ldquo;Because it seems like we already started our family.&rdquo;
His eyes widened. Hadn&rsquo;t she just claimed that she couldn&rsquo;t get pregnant from him due to being super?
&ldquo;That’s right,&rdquo; she once again answered his very thoughts. &ldquo;But apparently I was already pregnant when I drank the potion….&rdquo;
&ldquo;That was… something else,&rdquo; James exclaimed when the bond broke.
Michelle couldn&rsquo;t really disagree, but she didn&rsquo;t feel like answering right now. Enabling James to look this deep into her soul had taken its toll and used up the rest of her super energy. And as her body returned to it&rsquo;s normal state, the exhaustion hit her like a train. From one moment to the next the bond was gone, and they barely had gotten to the good stuff.
What was left was a feeling of loneliness she hadn&rsquo;t felt for several days. The fact that she was now in her plain state didn&rsquo;t help at all. She fought back tears and turned away from him.
&ldquo;Is everything alright?&rdquo; James asked.
&ldquo;Yes, everything is fine,&rdquo; she pouted.
&ldquo;You&rsquo;re a bad liar.&rdquo; He came closer. &ldquo;Are you hurt?&rdquo;
&ldquo;No, just exhausted. I&rsquo;ve been up for quite a while, you know?&rdquo;
&ldquo;That makes it two of us.&rdquo; He hugged her from behind. &ldquo;Still, that&rsquo;s not what it is, right?&rdquo;
Michelle almost shivered. Right now she felt very self-conscious. She hadn&rsquo;t expected things to get that… private. After taking the leap of faith of showing him the mistakes of her past, she had intended to make it up by showing him all the incredible things she had done after her transformation. The problem was that even she wasn&rsquo;t proud of them.
&ldquo;I&rsquo;m just a naïve fool that happened to be extremely lucky, am I not?&rdquo; she said.
&ldquo;What? You&rsquo;re not a fool! What makes you think that way?&rdquo;
Michelle sighed. &ldquo;All the things I did with these powers, they weren&rsquo;t that much to speak of.&rdquo;
&ldquo;That&rsquo;s not true! You saved people after all!&rdquo;
&ldquo;I only delayed things for Erika! I didn&rsquo;t save her at all. In fact she was already safe when I interfered. I only made things worse.&rdquo; After everything that had happened today, this was still the harsh reality.
&ldquo;You made a mistake, fixed it, and learned from it. That&rsquo;s a win in my book. And I didn&rsquo;t mean Erika, there were others, too.&rdquo;
The image of the young girl popped up in her head. &ldquo;Everybody can jump into the flames or catch a bullet when they are invulnerable,&rdquo; she sadly announced. &ldquo;Nothing special about me doing that then.&rdquo;
&ldquo;You couldn&rsquo;t be more wrong!&rdquo; James almost shouted. &ldquo;After all, you did it, not someone else. By now we know that there&rsquo;s someone passing around these powers, yet none of them has done anything like you did. Sure, you may be lucky to have found the seed, but of the five supers I met today, you&rsquo;re the only one who’s helped anybody. Actually you&rsquo;re the only one who didn&rsquo;t use her powers to hurt or steal at all!&rdquo;
That comforted her a bit. Being the one out of five did raise her confidence a bit.
&ldquo;Besides,&rdquo; James continued. &ldquo;Given that you were the one that was all over the news today, it may the reason things change in the future. If someone gets these powers in the near future, they will be reminded of you and either follow your example or at least refrain from causing trouble out of fear you might deal with them.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Aww,&rdquo; Michelle turned around to face him again. &ldquo;You&rsquo;re just saying that to cheer me up!&rdquo;
&ldquo;I&rsquo;m serious. You&rsquo;re carrying a lot of weight on your shoulders, and you&rsquo;re past the point where you can bail out easily. So I figured you need all the support you can get&hellip; and I&rsquo;m terribly sorry to not have given it to you right away earlier.&rdquo;
He leaned in for a kiss that somehow helped to wash all her bad feelings away. Despite her weakened state, she could feel their connection again. And through that connection she could hear one thought loud and clear:
If she asks me again, I won&rsquo;t say no.

Deziree turned around to spot a woman hovering there. She wore a black catsuit with red and orange flames on it that seemed to flow straight into the boots she wore.
That outfit only enhanced the long red hair and the glowing orange eyes as well as the proportions that were almost identical to Deziree&rsquo;s own. If she had to describe this woman with one word, it would definitely be &lsquo;hot&rsquo;.
&ldquo;Uhm&hellip;thanks,&rdquo; Deziree answered shyly. From what she had heard about this woman, she had hospitalized a man she had encountered. The good news was that the victim claimed it to be an accident. But Deziree had no way of knowing if that was true, so she kept her guard up. After all, the other woman could probably see what was inside the containers. Unfortunately the redhead seemed to have more of the super energy inside her than Deziree did right now.
&ldquo;No need to belittle yourself,&rdquo; the other woman said with a slightly warmer voice. &ldquo;This is the fanciest dress I&rsquo;ve seen that was created this way. It shows that you have a certain talent. Say, what should I call you?&rdquo;
&ldquo;I&rsquo;d rather keep my name a secret,&rdquo; Deziree answered immediately. After her encounter with the guard just now, she found it hard to believe this woman&rsquo;s friendly voice&hellip;not while she carried something with her that the other woman probably wanted.
&ldquo;I didn&rsquo;t ask for your real name, did I? By the way, you can call me Devil.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Not exactly the friendliest name there is. But it kinda fits.&rdquo; Now Deziree tried to figure out a name she could give in return. She hadn&rsquo;t really thought about a codename of the likes of Angel or Devil and actually wondered if the former had done such a thing. The media obviously named her because of the wings she had materialized to carry the plane after all. &ldquo;I can&rsquo;t really think of a name right now,&rdquo; she admitted.
&ldquo;Hm?&rdquo; The redhead raised her brow. &ldquo;Well, it&rsquo;s not that important actually. But I&rsquo;d like to ask you a few other questions. Would you answer them?&rdquo;
&ldquo;That depends on the question.&rdquo; Deziree was still on the fence about this woman. She was nice and polite, but maybe that was only because she thought she had the upper hand? Then again this was an opportunity to get some answers herself. &ldquo;Actually, I also have some questions about you. How about we take turns?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Fair enough. You can start if you want.&rdquo;
Now this was a surprise. The redhead let her start? Deziree hoped that this wasn&rsquo;t just a trick to make her trust the other woman. After the rotten guard, she could really use someone to restore her faith in humanity. &ldquo;How did you get these powers?&rdquo;
The redhead sighed. &ldquo;Straight to the chase, huh? Well since I&rsquo;m going to ask you the same it&rsquo;s only fair, I guess. My best friend got her hands on some of the stuff that&rsquo;s probably in those containers you carry and shared it with me.&rdquo;
&ldquo;How did she get it?&rdquo; Deziree asked.
&ldquo;Wait, first you&rsquo;ll have to answer me my question. How did you get these powers?&rdquo;
Deziree sighed. &ldquo;Some superpowered bitch tried to kill me, got her hands on one of these containers, drank a great deal of it, and started leaking milk. The Angel interfered, kicked the bitches' ass while I managed to sneak some of the milk away, and you can guess the rest.&rdquo;
Devil&rsquo;s orange eyes widened. &ldquo;Interesting. Your turn again.&rdquo;
&ldquo;How did your friend get this stuff? Did she have another person who gave it to her? Or does she have a plant that produces it?&rdquo;
&ldquo;She&rsquo;s got her own plant. So the milk you drank came from another super? Where did her powers come from? These containers, or somewhere else?&rdquo;
Deziree shrugged. &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t know. She seemed unaware of the stuffs effects until she drank it, but I can&rsquo;t rule out that she got her powers through this.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Understandable. Well, your turn again.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Is your best friend the Angel?&rdquo;
For a second, Devil glared at her, but her expression softened right away. &ldquo;Guess there&rsquo;s no use hiding it: Yes. My turn again: Where did those containers come from?&rdquo;
&ldquo;I … uhm kinda stole them.&rdquo; Deziree admitted sheepishly. &ldquo;And if the Angel is really your best friend she knows from where.&rdquo; Or who I am, she thought to herself. &ldquo;What kinds of abilities do we all possess? It&rsquo;s kind of a hassle figuring everything out myself.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Well,&rdquo; Devil hesitated. &ldquo;The whole thing is a bit more complicated. From what I understand there&rsquo;s some basic abilities we gained through drinking the potion. From what I understand abilities like flight, invulnerability, energy-absorption and the ability to create this cloth-like material come straight from the plant that produced the potion, while other abilities like super strength, super senses, X-ray vision and super pheromones are basically just enhancements of normal human abilities. Anything else seems kind of individual.&rdquo;
&ldquo;What do you mean by that?&rdquo;
Devil looked at her, unsure about whether or not to protest about this follow-up question. She decided to answer instead. &ldquo;From what I understand we can use the aforementioned powers on an instinctive level, but it is also possible to figure out other abilities for yourself. And you can actually share these abilities with other supers by absorbing their super energy, so they&rsquo;re not really exclusive although they seem to be affected by one&rsquo;s personality.&rdquo;
Deziree&rsquo;s eyes widened.
&ldquo;Alright, my turn: What power that I didn&rsquo;t mention do you possess?&rdquo; Devil continued.
&ldquo;Uhm,&rdquo; Deziree pondered her answer. While invisibility would be the honest answer, she actually had some choices here. She had at least three abilities that wouldn&rsquo;t be among the standard set Devil had mentioned. The question was which one was hers? Well, mind control was obviously Susan&rsquo;s trick. That woman was so accustomed of getting what she wanted, that this power fit her far too well. That left heat vision and invisibility. And it was just as obvious that the latter fit for plain, shy unnoticeable Deziree.
&ldquo;I can shoot lasers out of my eyes,&rdquo; Deziree answered.
Devil&rsquo;s face could barely contain her surprise. &ldquo;First the dress and now that,&rdquo; she muttered to herself. &ldquo;What else?&rdquo;
&ldquo;What makes you think there is more?&rdquo; Deziree countered, wondering what that had to do with her dress.
Instead of answering, Devil held up her arm, looked at it and suddenly fired two beams of light onto it – beams that didn&rsquo;t hurt her in the least. &ldquo;Heat vision is kind of my thing. And actually your dress is too fancy for it to be created with the basic fabric creation, so I think you got an enhancement on that just like I did. It probably won&rsquo;t even disappear once you transform back.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Y-you said that these powers can be shared quite easily,&rdquo; Deziree stammered, her mind racing. She remembered how she had absorbed the energy from the bandage the Angel had given her. Apparently she had gotten all the Angel&rsquo;s abilities along with it. &ldquo;So you gave the Angel your powers…&rdquo;
&ldquo;Indeed. And apparently she gave them to you in turn,&rdquo; Devil concluded.
Deziree let out a sigh of relief. This confirmed that Devil was indeed a friend of the Angel. After the guard that had tried to lie to her before, it mean a lot that this woman spoke the truth. Then it hit her: She had absorbed the Angels powers&hellip; the same Angel that had easily defeated Susan earlier today.
&ldquo;Wow&hellip; I didn&rsquo;t look at it this way,&rdquo; she exclaimed.
&ldquo;So, what extra powers do you have?&rdquo; Devil repeated.
&ldquo;Well, I can turn invisible,&rdquo; Deziree admitted, before remembering that Devil would probably learn about Susan&rsquo;s ability if she asked the Angel. &ldquo;And I kinda have mind control powers.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Mind control?&rdquo; Devil seemed intrigued. &ldquo;That&rsquo;s sounds dangerous.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Yeah,&rdquo; Deziree nodded. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s from the woman whose milk I drank and&hellip; let&rsquo;s just say she didn&rsquo;t notice what she was actually capable of. Thank goodness&hellip;she wasn&rsquo;t exactly subtle. Who knows what she could have done without anybody to stop her.&rdquo;
Devil nodded, and after a moment of silence she added. &ldquo;Your turn.&rdquo;
This brought Deziree back to their asking game. She had a lot of questions, but right now it was hard for her to figure out the right one. &ldquo;Uhm, why did you approach me instead of&hellip; y&rsquo;know grab those containers or something like that?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Hm,&rdquo; Devil took some time to prepare the right words. &ldquo;In my experience it&rsquo;s a lot more constructive to talk to one another instead of showing hostility. After all, you probably wouldn&rsquo;t want to answer my questions if I attacked you out of the blue. And these containers&hellip;if they got damaged in the struggle the contents would rain upon the city. I can&rsquo;t even imagine the damage that could cause.&rdquo;
There was no arguing with that.
&ldquo;My turn,&rdquo; Devil continued. &ldquo;Since you had the choice to become super, why did you drink that milk? What exactly are your goals?&rdquo;
As simple as it sounded, as embarrassing was the answer. Deziree blushed as she thought about her original reasons behind drinking this potion. She hadn&rsquo;t done that for the ability to rip open a vault door with her bare hands or the ability to bend other&rsquo;s minds to her will.
&ldquo;I … uhm kinda did it for the looks,&rdquo; she almost whispered.
Devil raised her eyebrow. Given that they were hovering high over the city, the wind would usually make it impossible for her to hear Deziree, but her super hearing made up for that.
&ldquo;I mean, well&hellip;I looked rather plain before I took it and&hellip; when I encountered these women today, not only the Angel, but the one who attacked me as well. They just make you want to be like them, in a way.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Yeah, I know that feeling,&rdquo; Devil nodded. &ldquo;But now that you have these looks, what are you gonna do with them? Especially since you got yourself quite the supply of them.&rdquo;
She gestured at the containers that Deziree was still holding. Normally she would have struggled to carry even one of them, but right now the two had felt so light to her that she had almost forgotten about them. Then again, their valuable contents had kept them in the back of her head.
Her mind darted back and forth. Deziree hadn&rsquo;t planned ahead that far. Getting a large enough supply had been the natural thing to do - and the chaos at the lab had made it easier for her to get that. But aside from that&hellip;
&ldquo;You haven&rsquo;t thought that far, have you?&rdquo; Devil eventually spoke it out.
Deziree let her head hang low in defeat. &ldquo;It was a spontaneous decision.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Don&rsquo;t beat yourself up because of that. It was even worse for me,&rdquo; the redhead cheered her up. &ldquo;I was heartbroken and my best friend had entrusted some of the potion to me. When I got sick on top of that I couldn&rsquo;t resist any longer.&rdquo;
Raising her head again, Deziree managed to fill in the blanks. She had heard about Devil&rsquo;s encounter with Mr. Riley, but since that wasn&rsquo;t as well known as the Angel, she couldn&rsquo;t mention it right now. What&rsquo;s more, she knew that this guy had an affair with Susan Harland of all people. The same woman who had intended to kill Deziree for no reason at all.
&ldquo;Well, I guess we all make mistakes,&rdquo; she commented. &ldquo;What exactly are you planning to do with your abilities?&rdquo;
&ldquo;If you asked me a week ago I would have said &lsquo;become a superheroine, of course&rsquo; but now this doesn&rsquo;t seem too smart. That spot is occupied by Angel, after all, and stepping into the spotlight would only make it harder for her. For now I&rsquo;m trying to get my life back on track and since I always wanted to be a doctor, I thought maybe I, with all these outrageous powers, I might somehow develop actual healing powers. Of course&hellip;that&rsquo;s a work in progress.&rdquo;
&ldquo;That sounds quite ambitious,&rdquo; Deziree concluded. &ldquo;But an honorable goal nonetheless.&rdquo;
&ldquo;There are some personal reasons behind that, too. I&rsquo;m trying to solve a tricky problem with these powers and actually&hellip;&rdquo; she averted her eyes as she sheepishly finished the sentence. &ldquo;I could really use some of the stuff from these containers for that.&rdquo;
Deziree gulped as she heard that. &ldquo;W-what do you mean, I thought the Angel shared her supply with you?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Yeah she does, but it&rsquo;s kinda important for it to be of a different source than the one she has. You know the stuff changed our genes, and two people who took the potion from the same source would be like siblings. This might work with good friends, but for the partner&hellip; it&rsquo;s pretty much incestuous. A potion from another source however would mean that the changes were slightly different - no incest there.&rdquo;
No, thought Desiree, that actually made sense. &ldquo;So that explains why the Angel took the remainder of the third container with her.&rdquo;
Devil looked at her, surprised, but nodded eventually. &ldquo;Well, in that case she might be having the time of her life right now.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Dammit!&rdquo; Michelle screamed as her fist slammed into the boulder. The giant rock crumbled under the force, and with a loud boom shattered into thousands of tiny pieces that flew in every possible direction.
The young woman looked around. By now she had turned a large part of the mountain front into a number of small stones. Any mining company would be proud of that, but for her it was merely a way to vent her frustration. In her mind she replayed her last conversation with James, which hadn&rsquo;t gone entirely as planned. Now that she had found an alternative power source for him, she had intended for him to take it only for him to decline out of fear for the consequences. Unfortunately she couldn&rsquo;t take that away from him. There was at least one person who died because she had taken the potion - so it was hard to argue with that no matter how convinced she was that everything would be alright. Then there had been the part about her wanting to get knocked up by him. Michelle knew that from an instinctive part this made sense - and that may actually be a subconscious reason for her. But still, she didn&rsquo;t want to admit to herself that her wishes and desires all boiled down to a wish to procreate.
Focusing the super energy in her eyes, two beams of blue light shot out of them and cut another boulder from the mountain. The rock fell towards her only for another punch of hers to shatter it just like the one before. Michelle had always wondered what she should use her destructive powers for, and now she had the answer: Nothing helped her vent her own anger better than senseless destruction. In the last five minutes she had caused more destruction than in her entire life before that. Fortunately, nobody would mourn the mountain she disfigured. There was nobody in the vicinity anyway.
Eventually, however she got bored with that. As much a stress reliever it was, the whole thing didn&rsquo;t bring her any closer to a solution. To find that, she would need to talk to someone and get a third opinion. Rising up from the mountain, she instantly accelerated to make her way back home. Compared to last night, Michelle&rsquo;s flight speed had significantly improved. The whole exertion with the plane had worked wonders on that front. Using all her cells to fly now seemed so easy, as if it had become a part of her. From the mountain in Africa to her hometown in the US it took a mere ten minutes - and she wasn&rsquo;t even going full speed yet. She probably could fly around the world in twenty minutes instead of the almost full hour she had needed yesterday.
Once she was back in familiar airspace, she quickly scanned Amanda&rsquo;s apartment - only to see Amanda wasn&rsquo;t there. Michelle let out a disappointed frown. Amanda was the only other person that knew about her powers. Who else could she talk to about such a matter?
It took Amanda a while to get used to the smell in the bar. This was the first time she had visited in her super form and her enhanced senses were picking up more different scents than she was comfortable with. Next to her, Desire had struggled with the same problems. The decision to move their conversation from the skyline to a more hospitable place had more or less forced the other woman to come up with a codename and this had been it. Amanda didn&rsquo;t think that Desire described the other woman well, though. Compared to any normal woman, she surely was a living fantasy, but compared to other supers like herself she didn&rsquo;t stick ut that much. Their physiques were so similar that it was a matter of personal taste after all. Still, she didn&rsquo;t complain about the name, especially since Desire had actually agreed to share a whole container of the super potion with Amanda. That was much more than she needed, and she definitely appreciated the gesture.
The two superwomen had changed their outfits into something more fitting for the occasion, but that didn&rsquo;t mean they didn&rsquo;t draw any attention. On the contrary, given the stares they were receiving, Amanda doubted that her Devil costume would have drawn any more attention than she had now. Desire smiled and blushed at all these eyes that were aimed at her. Amanda had the feeling that Desire enjoyed this quite a lot. Maybe the name wasn&rsquo;t that far off after all. They chose a hidden corner booth for themselves.
&ldquo;So what exactly are you doing at that research institute?&rdquo; Amanda resumed their conversation.
&ldquo;Funny thing: I&rsquo;m a botanist.&rdquo; Desire continued, &ldquo;I had that stuff right in front of my nose for the last few months and had no idea what it was capable of.&rdquo;
That surprised Amanda less than expected. Michelle and her had already theorized that the plant was alien and it made sense that there was more than one seed inside the meteor. Of course it would have been found.
&ldquo;I can see that. Drinking some alien plant juice isn&rsquo;t exactly a valid form of examination.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Oh it would have been one hell of a surprise,&rdquo; Desire chuckled. &ldquo;But I&rsquo;m glad that it happened in my own apartment, I couldn&rsquo;t stand the idea of being filmed when it happened.&rdquo;
She blushed. Amanda could all to well understand why she did so. Even though the first transformation started as a rough ride, it did finish as a really pleasurable one.
&ldquo;Uhm, there&rsquo;s one question I am particularly interested in&hellip;&rdquo; Desire blushed even further. Amanda wouldn&rsquo;t be surprised if the other woman suddenly started glowing bright red if she got any more embarrassed. Stranger things had happened.
&ldquo;Shoot it.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Well&hellip;&rdquo; her voice became a whisper. &ldquo;Is it actually possible for us to have s-sex with normal men?&rdquo;
Amanda could barely prevent herself from laughing. &ldquo;Of course it is,&rdquo; she said before adding with a smile. &ldquo;And it feels awesome!&rdquo;
Desire&rsquo;s eyes grew wide as her lips curled to a smile. Amanda could even see that the other woman rose into the air - probably involuntarily.
&ldquo;Keep it together,&rdquo; she whispered. &ldquo;We&rsquo;re in public, after all.&rdquo;
Blushing again, Desire sank back onto her seat. &ldquo;Sorry, I&rsquo;m new to that.&rdquo; A quick glance revealed that her little trip to the air had gone unnoticed. &ldquo;All clear it seems.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Back to your job. You said you examined the plant, did you find anything out of the ordinary besides this liquid?&rdquo;
Desire thought a bit. &ldquo;Well, I wouldn&rsquo;t call it out of the ordinary since it&rsquo;s an alien life form. The similarity to local plant life is quite striking. Oh, and it&rsquo;s quite tough. We tried to cut off a leaf for sampling, but no matter what we tried, we couldn&rsquo;t do it. Until yesterday I had no idea how to explain it, but after seeing the Angel carrying the plane this morning, I immediately had a feeling that this could be connected.&rdquo;
Amanda was about to comment, when a waitress arrived at the table. To her surprise she already brought two beers and put them on their table.
&ldquo;From the two young men at the bar,&rdquo; she announced and pointed to towards them.
The two men in question were admittedly handsome and seemed to have the money to spare. Their cheeky grins basically claimed &ldquo;We&rsquo;re the best you can get here&rdquo; and Amanda didn&rsquo;t stand this kind of arrogance. Desire however returned the smile.
&ldquo;Which one do you want?&rdquo; she asked.
&ldquo;My fiancé,&rdquo; Amanda answered right away. &ldquo;Not one of these guys.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Oh? I thought you were heartbroken before you took the potion?&rdquo;
Amanda bit her lip, this topic was quite close to unmasking her.
&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s just say it worked out somehow,&rdquo; she commented, hoping to end the topic quickly.
&ldquo;Come to think of it, didn&rsquo;t you deliver a guy to the hospital a few days ago? Had that anything to do with it?&rdquo;
Now Amanda was getting nervous. The other woman knew a lot more than she expected. &ldquo;Uhm, well&hellip;&rdquo; she stammered. &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t want to talk about that.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Oh come on,&rdquo; the brunette urged. &ldquo;If that was an accident, you could tell me how it happened. After all something similar could happen with me as well. You also all but know who I am anyway. All you have to do is ask your friend and she&rsquo;ll be able to identify me.&rdquo;
Amanda let out a sigh. Desire had a point. &ldquo;Ok, I&rsquo;ll admit it. He was my ex-boyfriend at the time. It&rsquo;s complicated. He had cheated on me, so I dumped him. And I took the potion right after he had fetched his stuff from my place. I went for a flight through the city and found myself at his place as he was about to arrive. Given that I looked radically different I wanted to use that as I flirted with him a bit.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I take it he was like wax in your hands?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Actually he wasn&rsquo;t. On the contrary he was more affected by the breakup than I expected. Unfortunately I didn&rsquo;t realize that and kicked his car to bits and then took him for a quick flight - too bad his shirt couldn&rsquo;t carry his weight.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Ouch&hellip; hard to believe that this still worked out in the end.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Well, it&rsquo;s a bit complicated. There were circumstances behind his cheating, stuff that I hadn&rsquo;t known before and that allowed me to make an exception for him.&rdquo;
Desire listened intently and nodded. &ldquo;So you didn&rsquo;t know about his condition? I mean a terminal sickness isn&rsquo;t a small deal.&rdquo;
Amanda&rsquo;s eyes widened. &ldquo;H-how did you know that?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Well, I&rsquo;ve had the questionable honor of playing babysitter for the woman your ex had an affair with. Let&rsquo;s just say every encounter got worse - until she tried to kill me today.&rdquo;
&ldquo;What?&rdquo; Amanda almost crushed her drink as she heard that. &ldquo;That Harland bitch is super?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Not anymore. She may still look like it, but her powers were gone when the Angel was done with her.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I don&rsquo;t understand. She still looked super even when she was out of energy?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Yes. Is that strange? I thought people would turn back to normal once out of power, but after seeing that I imagined that I&rsquo;d get to keep these,&rdquo; Desire pointed at her chest.
Shaking her head Amanda tried to figure this out. &ldquo;No, we usually transform back to normal. Well not really, we still look better than before but can still be recognized as our original selves. It would be the first time I heard about someone looking super even after being out of energy.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Interesting,&rdquo; Desire commented. &ldquo;So despite our deep-rooted changes into half-alien hybrids, we still look perfectly human when we run out of energy? This sounds a bit like that is supposed to conserve said energy.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Indeed. And in the long run it should be possible for us to absorb sunlight to produce the super energy ourselves.&rdquo;
Now Desire seemed surprised. &ldquo;That doesn&rsquo;t make much sense strictly speaking. The amount of energy in the sunlight is far too low to allow any of the stuff we can do. Especially compared to the amount of liquid the plant can produce.&rdquo;
&ldquo;You may have a point there, but I can definitely feel how the sunlight gets absorbed and turned into super energy - even though it&rsquo;s not much. If anything it is a catalyst the plants and our bodies need to produce super energy. Right now we&rsquo;re rather bad at it which explains why we deplete our supply. At one point however, we&rsquo;ll be producing more than we use up.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Oh god that&rsquo;s it!&rdquo; Desire exclaimed. &ldquo;I know why Susan didn&rsquo;t transform back to normal! She had drunk so much of the potion at once that she reached the maximum she could store. That&rsquo;s why she lactated the excess energy as an own potion. For her body this must&rsquo;ve been a sign that she didn&rsquo;t need the &lsquo;low power&rsquo; state anymore.&rdquo;
&ldquo;So all it needs is drinking enough potion and we&rsquo;d be stuck like this?&rdquo; Amanda whispered. Part of her liked the double identity she could have as her normal self and Devil. As good as it felt to be Devil, she had a normal life that she could live. How would that affect her life with Fred if that happened? Her eyes widened. She had spent hours looking through her medical books to figure out a way to cure his Harland Syndrome and how the potion had proven fatal for Erika. Could this be the solution?
&ldquo;You don&rsquo;t look like that&rsquo;s a bad thing&hellip;&rdquo; Desire commented.
&ldquo;Well I just had an idea. But I would need some information first. You see the potion proved deadly for someone with Harland Syndrome, and I need to verify the cause of death. If it&rsquo;s the transformation back to normal, then the whole not transforming back part could be the solution to curing the Harland Syndrome.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Haha that would be it,&rdquo; Desire chuckled. &ldquo;For Susan Harland to find the cure her father searched his whole life, it sounds a bit ironic. But for the cause of death I suggest you ask the one doing the autopsy.&rdquo; And with a nod towards the door she added. &ldquo;And it seems like you&rsquo;re lucky.&rdquo;
Jacob suppressed a yawn as they entered the bar. He had spent the last nights in bars hoping to find any clue on the superwomen that had appeared. Monday night he might have encountered a male version of these, but he had faced into the wrong direction. Last night on his way home he had been lucky to encounter the Angel. That was about it in terms of success and given today&rsquo;s events he had looked forward to an evening of peace and quiet.
Apparently James had thought otherwise. That in itself was a new development. Outside of work the two had never hung out and from the tone of him when he called, James had something on his mind that he wanted to drown in alcohol.
&ldquo;Two beers,&rdquo; James ordered the first round.
