Erika blinked a few times, showing that she was surprised. &ldquo;He told you about this?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Yes, a few months ago when he had the flu. I thought this was just a joke to prevent me from nursing him too much. Did he really break up with a girl because she went overboard when it came to nursing him?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Um, yeah. But she really had it coming. She tried to nurse him, even when he was fine.&rdquo; Erika took a deep breath. &ldquo;What I wanted to say is that you shouldn&rsquo;t exaggerate his condition. Don&rsquo;t give the impression that you only made up with him because of that and you should be fine.&rdquo;
Amanda sighed. Now she had to downplay an injury she herself had caused.
The date was going great from James' perspective. They had reached the restaurant without any complications, chit-chatting the whole way. Once they had taken their seats and placed their orders, their conversations drifted to their jobs.
&ldquo;… long story short, I&rsquo;m an assistant,&rdquo; Michelle finished her rather long job description.
&ldquo;So, technically you&rsquo;re a full-fledged reporter, but you don&rsquo;t actually appear on TV? Why is that?&rdquo;
&ldquo;I&rsquo;m quite shy and when I started, other candidates proved more useful in front of the camera. So I settled for the second row.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Do you have any intention of changing that? You don&rsquo;t seem that shy to me and I&rsquo;m sure you&rsquo;d make a great anchorwoman.&rdquo;
Michelle blushed and looked away, all while trying to hide her smile. God, she&rsquo;s adorable when she&rsquo;s embarrassed. James couldn&rsquo;t help but smile as well.
&ldquo;I did think about it, of course. But after a while I got used to my job and thanks to recent events I&rsquo;m really not interested in this kind of promotion anymore.&rdquo;
&ldquo;What recent events are you talking about?&rdquo;
&ldquo;The meteor scare of course. Can you imagine how it felt to see my colleagues adding fuel to the fire by concentrating on the worst case scenario which ended up being missed by several miles?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Oh yeah right, the media wasn&rsquo;t exactly helpful back then. But wouldn&rsquo;t that encourage you to change the way information is handled?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Easier said than done. When the whole industry only seeks sensation it becomes hard to change it all by yourself.”
James could easily empathize with her; after all he had a few things he didn’t like about his own job as well.
“How about yourself?” Michelle suddenly continued. “What does a scientific consultant for the police actually do when he’s not knocking on my door on a Sunday morning?”
&ldquo;Oh that&rsquo;s simple. When the police finds something out of the ordinary, they call me to check whether it really is.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Out of the ordinary? Did they expect small green men to come out of the meteor?&rdquo;
&ldquo;No, but the public already feared that a rock from outer space could bring the end of the world. The program is more to calm it down, actually. Unfortunately, this means most of my cases are downright boring and the police used this fact to get some additional tests done that they can&rsquo;t do due to budget or time constraints.&rdquo;
&ldquo;That doesn&rsquo;t sound too bad,&rdquo; Michelle said. &ldquo;My superiors would turn it into a corruption scandal, though.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Why is that?&rdquo;
&ldquo;You&rsquo;re doing work meant for the police while neglecting your own - that&rsquo;s the part that they would focus on. The fact that your job consists of helping the police would mean nothing to them.&rdquo;
James suddenly felt anxious. &ldquo;And what is your opinion about that?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Me? Well, you&rsquo;re doing your job and by assisting the police you&rsquo;re actually doing a public service, so it&rsquo;s hard to find anything wrong with that. The only &lsquo;out of the ordinary&rsquo; case I know about is some boulder that had been moved. By the way, are there any news on that one?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Actually&hellip;&rdquo; A sudden shudder went over James. He did have a theory about how that boulder got moved, but it might be a big mistake to share it with Michelle. She was part of the media after all. Spreading the news of superpowered women flying around would be just another day at work for her - not to mention a boost for her career. And he would be the security leak. This was one big dilemma. Until now everything had went great between Michelle and him, he honestly believed that there was some kind of connection between them. Still there was the possibility that those feelings were one-sided on his part and that she was merely using him. No! He needed to get rid of this paranoid thinking as soon as possible or otherwise it would poison the whole evening. &ldquo;… I&rsquo;m still operating on the &lsquo;a person lifted it&rsquo; theory.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I thought you said this boulder was too heavy to be lifted without proper equipment.&rdquo; James was surprised that, instead of laughing at such an outlandish idea, Michelle asked in barely a whisper.
&ldquo;Let me show you,&rdquo; there was only one way to go for James, but this didn&rsquo;t make him feel any better about it. He took out his smartphone and began looking for the video file that would explain his theory. Once he had found it, he presented it to Michelle.
It wasn&rsquo;t like it had been this afternoon where he had presented this video to a couple that had already heard about the existence of superpowers before. Hell, the man had even met one of them before. James watched as Michelle&rsquo;s eyes stayed fixated on the small screen in her hand. Concern was written all over her face. This was to be expected; after all she didn&rsquo;t know that the hostage would survive.
&ldquo;Why are you showing this to me?&rdquo; Michelle asked in a shaky voice once she was done watching.
&ldquo;You asked about the boulder, right? My theory is that she - or someone like her - moved it.&rdquo;
&ldquo;S-someone like her?&rdquo; Michelle seemed like she was about to freak out. &ldquo;Are there more like her around?&rdquo;
&ldquo;There&rsquo;s been word of a redheaded woman,&rdquo; again James was surprised at his own honesty. He realized that while he didn&rsquo;t know whether or not he could trust her, this honesty could come back to bite him. &ldquo;Excuse me for a second.&rdquo;
James then stood up and made his way to the bathroom, leaving his phone with the compromising video behind.
Sitting alone at the table, Michelle&rsquo;s tried to organize her panicked thoughts. How much did he know? Why did he even tell her about such an important discovery? Just because she asked? No, he most likely suspected her already; this was the most logical explanation. Did he just want her to make a mistake that proved his suspicions? It didn&rsquo;t feel that way. Actually it felt more like it was quite the opposite, like he didn&rsquo;t want her to confirm his fears. Michelle hadn&rsquo;t missed that James was nervous. In fact his nervousness had been contagious as it was the main reason she was nervous as well. Michelle noticed that James' phone was still lying in front of her. She wished she could just delete this video of her and be done with this story. But she knew things wouldn&rsquo;t be so easy. Sooner or later her actions would become public knowledge. It was a miracle that this video hadn&rsquo;t made it to the news yet. Most of her colleagues would simply take the camera or copy the file to present it to the world. Michelle was pretty sure that even if it wasn&rsquo;t her on the video, she wouldn&rsquo;t want to spread this news. Maybe she could convince James not to show it to anybody he met. It would calm her down if he agreed, after all.
James splashed cold water on his face. He had barely managed to set a trap that would decide whether or not Michelle was trustworthy - or if he had already screwed up by showing her the video. Thankfully he had some nasty surprises hidden on his phone that would make any attempt to copy the video file futile. The only way to publish this video was to steal the phone right now - in which case Michelle wouldn&rsquo;t be waiting for him at the table anymore. And if she was, a quick check on his phone would prove whether she had tried to copy it. He had made these precautions more out of legal reasons, so that he couldn&rsquo;t become a security leak should he lose his phone. To think that it would help him ease his unreasonable paranoia had a certain irony to it.
James returned to their table and smiled once he spotted Michelle still sitting there. Once he sat down, he picked up his phone and checked the file - and his smile grew even broader. Why had he even thought this woman was capable of something so underhanded?
&ldquo;What&rsquo;s the good news?&rdquo; Michelle asked.
&ldquo;I just noticed that you&rsquo;re just as nice as you look.&rdquo; Okay, that one was cheesy, but Michelle blushed nonetheless. &ldquo;You didn&rsquo;t try to copy this video file, meaning that showing it to you wasn&rsquo;t a mistake.&rdquo;
&ldquo;That&rsquo;s good to hear,&rdquo; Michelle indeed seemed to be relieved. James was just happy that she wasn&rsquo;t offended by him fearing such things. &ldquo;I already wondered why you showed me such delicate information in the first place. Do you have any idea what would happen if this got published?&rdquo;
&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve given it some thought, but in the end there are too many unknown variables. The most important part would be the &ldquo;how&rdquo; it&rsquo;s published. And the meteor scare was a good demonstration of how not to. If this woman continues like this, she will sooner or later become public knowledge. It&rsquo;ll depend on how good a job she does to determine whether she inspires hope or fear.&rdquo;
&ldquo;What&rsquo;s your opinion about her, then?&rdquo;
James hadn&rsquo;t expected to hear this particular question. It seemed strange to talk about a totally different woman on a date, especially if he didn&rsquo;t know that other woman.
&ldquo;It&rsquo;s a bit unreal that there&rsquo;s a real person that seems to be more fitting for a comic book than reality. But from what I heard so far, she really seems to fit the term superhero, wouldn&rsquo;t you think?&rdquo;
&ldquo;There&rsquo;s no arguing on the &lsquo;super&rsquo; part, but I don&rsquo;t think she should be called a hero yet. From what I see, there&rsquo;s no actual danger for her during the whole fight. Her priority should have been the safety of the hostages, but instead she went after the criminals first. You can clearly see that she screwed up the moment the hostage got retaken. It was written all over her face.&rdquo;
&ldquo;You may be right, but things aren&rsquo;t as easy as they are in fiction. Getting the hostage to safety sounds easier than it might be, so maybe attacking the kidnappers first was the best chance she had?&rdquo;
&ldquo;And if she had a better way but didn&rsquo;t use it?&rdquo;
James shrugged his shoulders. &ldquo;Everybody makes mistakes, I guess. I don&rsquo;t think it would be that good to openly point them out. The point is that she wanted to help and succeeded. She&rsquo;s basically doing a public service, it&rsquo;s hard to find anything wrong about that.&rdquo;
Michelle turned her head away as she blushed once again. She must have recognized that he had returned her own statement about his work to her.
&ldquo;I take it you&rsquo;re a fan of hers, then.&rdquo;
James had to gulp hard. This was the most dangerous question she could&rsquo;ve asked, and that slight smirk that was still on her face made it clear that she knew this. She was messing with him!
&ldquo;I don&rsquo;t really want to use the term &lsquo;fan&rsquo; here as I don&rsquo;t really know that much about her. She&rsquo;s flying around helping people and unlike the police, I don&rsquo;t see her as a problem.&rdquo;
&ldquo;So the police doesn&rsquo;t like her?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Not her specifically, but the idea that there are people with superpowers can become quite disturbing. And while this woman really seems use her powers for good, others may not be that nice.&rdquo;
&ldquo;If there are others, right?&rdquo;
&ldquo;There are. I mentioned a redhead before who may be connected to her. She&rsquo;s only appeared once so far and even the victim admits it was an accident. But even if she&rsquo;s nicer than expected, the fact that there are two of them increases the chances that there are even more.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I see, so the cops are more concerned that there may be a criminal with these powers. Can&rsquo;t blame them for that.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Yeah, let&rsquo;s just hope those two women are the only ones.&rdquo; James thought about the dead prostitute and how she would fit into the story. Then he realized that their conversation had become quite serious and that this wasn&rsquo;t exactly the mood he had intended for this evening.
&ldquo;Do you have any theory as to how they got their powers?&rdquo; Michelle seemed to enjoy this topic, though. &ldquo;Could it be related to the meteor?&rdquo;
&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve got no idea,&rdquo; James admitted. &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve yet to receive the report as to what they found out about the meteor, but I doubt this will make any change. The best way to find out might be the woman herself, but that&rsquo;s not going to be easy. Well, there&rsquo;s still the autopsy.&rdquo;
&ldquo;What autopsy?&rdquo;
James wanted to mentally kick himself for even mentioning it, but found that he had begun to trust Michelle and valued her opinion.
&ldquo;The police found a drug victim that turned out to be somehow mutated. Her DNA contained many more chromosomes than the human DNA was supposed to have. A comparison with old hair of hers showed that she originally possessed the 23 pairs normal for humans, but at the time of her death possessed 27 additional pairs.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Any idea about what these extra chromosomes do?&rdquo;
&ldquo;None so far. The only outward sign was that she looked much more - uhm - healthy than she was supposed to.&rdquo;
&ldquo;And by healthy you mean more attractive?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Both. She had been a drug addict for quite some time, and it showed in past photos. The corpse I saw didn&rsquo;t show any signs of this, as if she had been at perfect health again. It seemed like her drug history had been cleared from her body - which most likely caused her death.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Any idea how that happened?&rdquo; Michelle now sounded really concerned.
Again, James had to shrug his shoulders. &ldquo;Your guess is as good as mine. My first idea was that it was caused by some kind of drugs. There&rsquo;s no hint so far that it&rsquo;s connected to the two superpowered women&rdquo; He tried to sound as convincing as possible, as he could see Michelle becoming more and more anxious - something he instinctively wanted to prevent. &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s change the subject, shall we? It&rsquo;s kind of awkward to talk about other women when the most beautiful woman in the world sits right in front of me.&rdquo;
Michelle rewarded his compliment with a smile.
Amanda entered her apartment with a loud sigh. Her head hurt like hell and Amanda knew full well why it did so. She had planned to make Erika spill the oh-so-big secret she and Fred were keeping from her, by getting her drunk. Normally, this would be a futile effort as Erika could hold her liquor quite well. Amanda had thought that increased resistance to alcohol would be one of the many tiny improvements she had been subjected to. And technically she was right, just not in the way she had expected. It took her only one drink to realize that she was getting drunk faster than she normally would. Her body processed the alcohol much faster, which included a fast approaching hangover. Of course, her plan to get Erika drunk was doomed to fail this way. Amanda considered herself lucky that Erika hadn&rsquo;t noticed her condition; after all she didn&rsquo;t need any more suspicion from her. Now she was at her apartment and her hangover hit her with full force. It was tempting to skip her suffering by drinking the super potion, but the last time she had done so had ended badly, so she would have to wait it through. After all, it wouldn&rsquo;t take that long for her to recover and she wanted to prove to herself that she wasn&rsquo;t reliant of the super potion.
Time sure flew by for Michelle and eventually she stared dumbfounded at her finished dessert, realizing that their dinner was about to end. She took a glance at James, who seemed to have similar thoughts. Except for the short moment where both of them had been almost afraid of each other, they had a really good time together. In fact, Michelle had absolutely no doubt that James dreaded the end of this evening just as much as she did. Now that she thought about it, it was a bit strange that she was so confident in knowing how James felt. This reminded her of how Amanda had claimed to know for a fact that Fred hadn&rsquo;t been lying about still loving her. It had sounded like wishful thinking back then, but right now Michelle understood what her best friend had meant. She felt somehow connected to James, and began to wonder if it was more than just a metaphor. Amanda&rsquo;s words were echoing in her mind: &lsquo;Just be yourself and determine whether or not you love him. If you do, and he loves you too, then you should tell him asap.&rsquo; Why did this pop up in her head now? Not too long ago, she had been scared of him finding out and now she was … curious.
&ldquo;About these superpowered women, you mentioned earlier. What is your job about them exactly?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Officially I&rsquo;m researching everything out of the ordinary, which includes them, of course.&rdquo;
&ldquo;So, you&rsquo;re hunting them?&rdquo;
&ldquo;That&rsquo;s what it boils down to. Chances of success are slim enough for my superiors to &lsquo;entrust&rsquo; this job to me and in case I do find something, they&rsquo;ll just let someone else handle it.&rdquo;
Michelle could clearly feel his anger over this situation and she had no trouble sympathizing with him about it.
&ldquo;That sounds quite demotivating. How do you keep yourself going?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Curiosity,&rdquo; James didn&rsquo;t even have to think for this answer. &ldquo;I became a scientist because of that and nobody can argue that my job has its exciting parts now.&rdquo;
&ldquo;But it sounds futile if you&rsquo;re not really able to research anything,&rdquo; Michelle retorted. &ldquo;What good is it to track something down if someone else steals the glory afterwards?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Good thing I&rsquo;ve got a certain amount of freedom, then. After all, they can&rsquo;t take away information that I already possess. They may have cut me off the mutated drug-addict, but I do know a few things about her - not to mention my connection to the police. They also know that there was a moved boulder in the mountains and that it was most likely moved by this blonde superchick, but I may have forgotten to mention the pajama pants that led me to you.&rdquo;
When he put it that way, it was a damn miracle that he still hadn&rsquo;t at least considered her to be involved.
&ldquo;Thanks, I really appreciate that.&rdquo;
&ldquo;It was nothing and it would&rsquo;ve left a bad first impression to draw any unnecessary attention towards you. You deserve better.&rdquo;
Michelle blushed at the honesty of that comment, and the unspoken affection that had caused him to act that way. He mainly wanted to help her - and he hadn&rsquo;t even intended to tell her this. The fact that she was above suspicion for him had played only a very small part in James not mentioning her to his superiors compared to this. Michelle also realized that the only reason she was above suspicion, were the radically different looks between her normal form and her super form. James simply hadn&rsquo;t considered the possibility that there was a physical transformation involved that turned her body into a living wet dream. One good thing about him not knowing her secret was that he didn&rsquo;t fall for her just for her super looks. Unable to hide her happiness about this, Michelle began to smile even more.
God, she&rsquo;s adorable when she smiles.
What was that? Michelle looked surprised at James, who was just in the process of drinking. It had sounded like his voice, but he clearly hadn&rsquo;t spoken. Must&rsquo;ve been someone else.
James paid for the meal and the two of them made their way back to his car. Neither of them said a word during the drive. Michelle didn&rsquo;t really pay attention to the road as she watched James from the side. He was focused on the traffic and used it as a means to ignore his nervousness. Her heart began to beat faster as she realized just how much he wanted this drive to last longer, to make a detour just to spend more time with her. But doing so, would startle her and so he did the only thing he could do, to prolong it: drive slowly. Fate was on his side as there was no free space before her apartment for him to park - or stop.
&ldquo;Seems like you&rsquo;ll have to park a little further away and walk me to my doorstep,&rdquo; Michelle teased.
James did as he was told - with a broad grin on his face that he thought invisible due to the darkness in the car. Once they had left the car, Michelle seized the opportunity and grabbed his arm so that they walked arm in arm. With great joy she remembered the couples she had watched on her first night on patrol. Right now she had no reason to be envious of them.
&ldquo;Well,&rdquo; James began as they had reached the door. &ldquo;I &hellip;uh&hellip; had a really good time tonight. I mean, you&rsquo;re a fascinating woman, that&hellip; no, what I wanted to say is&hellip;&rdquo;
Michelle interrupted James helpless stammering by gently putting her index finger onto his mouth.
&ldquo;You seem at a loss for words right now, so let me do the talking. I also had a fun time tonight and I&rsquo;d like to repeat it rather sooner than later. Yes, I know you were going to ask me that, because you&rsquo;re so much of a nice guy that you&rsquo;d rather ask this instead of what you really want to ask. So instead of trying to come up with the right words how about you try to come up with the right actions?&rdquo;
Even though it sounded as if James had a choice, the reality was that Michelle already had made it for him. As she spoke, her face had steadily gotten closer to his and in the end her finger seemed the only thing separating their mouths from each other. With their faces so close, they stared each other in the eyes. Michelle teased him for a little longer, savoring his undivided attention before finally removing her finger. Immediately their lips met and for Michelle this moment was magical. Never before in her life had she felt this happy - and considering the recent events in her life this really meant something. A stream of emotions washed over her. Michelle suddenly saw pictures of herself from another person’s view. From the angle it seemed like the other person was at least a foot taller than her, but Michelle didn&rsquo;t even need this information to realize that she was somehow seeing flashes of James' memories. Besides a few flashes that must&rsquo;ve been from their initial encounter yesterday, all of them were from this evening - including the very moment before their kiss. In this memory she seemed equal in height- a sign that reading his mind and feelings wasn&rsquo;t the only extraordinary thing Michelle was doing right now. Under normal circumstances these news would have been the focus of her attention. But right now, while she literally tasted his affections that only added to her own, Michelle didn&rsquo;t care about petty things like how she wasn&rsquo;t supposed to have any powers right now. And so the fact that she was hovering a foot above the floor remained unnoticed by the two lovers who had only one thing in their mind: Them.

The blonde woman hovered above the city trying to find an opportunity to put her superpowers to good use. It had been just over ten minutes since she left the parking block.
Michelle sighed. She was trying to get the hostage situation behind her by finding something else to do, but once again the young woman was reminded of the fact that such an opportunity wouldn’t arise just because she wanted to.
Even though she could see the entire city from her vantage point, Michelle couldn&rsquo;t see all the minute details at once. If she focused on a certain place with her super vision, she naturally ignored pretty much everything else&hellip; a bit disappointing, really. Then again her super eyesight was much more than any human could dream of – not to mention that she was near-sighted in her normal form. When her gaze fell on Amanda’s apartment, Michelle remembered that she had an appointment with her best friend and decided that this was as good a time as any to drop by.
One second was all it took to reach her best friend’s apartment. Nobody in the neighborhood was able to spot the blonde goddess who had just descended. Amanda herself was no exception, and she all but screamed in surprise as Michelle suddenly appeared in her living room.
“Don’t startle me like that!&quot; she said as she overcame the shock.
