&ldquo;If that&rsquo;s the only effect of – whatever this is – then I&rsquo;m sure everybody would want to get some of that.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I seriously doubt it. Too bad we won&rsquo;t be able to see any other effects with patient zero being dead.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Speaking of weird effects, do you think this is connected to the flying woman rumors I told you about earlier today?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Beats me. I don&rsquo;t want to consider such rumors until I see at least some proof. Something like a convincing photo or something.&rdquo;
Detective Spencer&rsquo;s cell phone suddenly started to ring, abruptly pausing their conversation. James used the opportunity to give the place another once-over. Why did this woman start to clean up at such an inconvenient moment? The original idea was that there were different women involved and the new one wanted to settle in accordingly, but this wasn&rsquo;t necessarily the case. Wait, maybe this cleaning session had also been caused by her improved health? The diary downright stated, that she felt great and wanted to start fresh. This would at least narrow down the moment when exactly the first effects were visible. Maybe the autopsy would give a bit more insight&hellip;
&ldquo;Really? You&rsquo;re not kidding?&rdquo; Jacob sounded really excited about whatever was the topic of his phone call. &ldquo;Alright, we&rsquo;ll be over there in a minute.&rdquo;
