&ldquo;What?&rdquo; Michelle asked, realizing too late that Amanda was X-Raying her, no she was already using this 3D-Model-Vision, she had originally intended.
&ldquo;You&rsquo;re … impressive,&rdquo; was all that Amanda said before letting her vision return to normal.
&ldquo;Sorry, I just needed to know if I can do it too. Now you, try to use heat vision.&rdquo;
Michelle did as she was told. She was sure that she had tried something extremely similar yesterday, but failed to do so nonetheless. Maybe she just wasn&rsquo;t able to use heat vision at all? Still, watching Amanda do it had made it really easy to grasp the concept behind it. This gave her confidence. Her blue eyes focused on the same boulder Amanda had used as target practice as she concentrated the energy in her eyes and&hellip; it worked. She could feel her vision turn into heat, and the exact spot she was looking at being disintegrated immediately.
&ldquo;Cool!&rdquo; said Amanda after Michelle was done.
&ldquo;I think the proper term is hot,&rdquo; Michelle corrected her.
&ldquo;Both fit for blue heat vision.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Point taken.&rdquo; Seems like the heat vision always has the same color as their eyes.
They spent a few minutes trying out their new super power. Since all they had to do to properly aim their heat vision was look at the intended target, this part was almost ridiculously easy. The challenge lay more in the intensity of the ray, as a too strong blast would not only cut through one rock, but also whatever was behind it. When they were sure that they could control their heat vision well enough to only lightly scorch the rock they used as target practice, both women agreed that there was little use in further training.
“When you look at it, this ability isn’t that useful,” Amanda began. “Best I can think of is this heating-the-gun-till-it’s-too-hot-to-hold-routine. It wouldn’t even be helpful against another person with superpowers.”
Michelle hadn’t actually considered this possibility. “Do you really think there are others with these powers?”
“Well you found the seed of your precious plant on the sidewalk, right? Chances are that there are more seeds somewhere. So it can’t hurt to prepare for the worst case scenario.”
&ldquo;People getting super powers and immediately deciding to go on a rampage because of it? I think that&rsquo;s a bit too pessimistic,&rdquo; Michelle sighed. &ldquo;But then again it is the worst case scenario.&rdquo;
&ldquo;My thoughts exactly. That&rsquo;s why I think it&rsquo;s crucial to master these powers as quickly as possible. So that you have the necessary experience to deal with any aspiring super villain.&rdquo;
&ldquo;That I have the necessary experience? What about you? Didn&rsquo;t we plan on becoming superheroines together?&rdquo;
&ldquo;I did say that, yes. But what I meant was that you would become the heroine and I the sidekick that eventually emerges. This didn&rsquo;t change just because I drank the potion earlier than anticipated.&rdquo;
Michelle was dumbfounded by this revelation. Earlier she had dismissed Amanda&rsquo;s belittling herself as caused by her guilt about her encounter with Fred, now she heard that Amanda had planned this even before that. But why? For years it had been Amanda who had been the more confident one, with Michelle more or less hiding behind her friend. Still, Michelle had always considered themselves to be on the same level.
&ldquo;Why does this sound like you are putting yourself below me?&rdquo; Michelle sounded more offended that she intended to.
Amanda sighed. &ldquo;That&rsquo;s not how I mean it. I just don&rsquo;t think it&rsquo;s good for two &lsquo;super chicks&rsquo; to appear at the same time. People would just get us confused with each other. So it&rsquo;s better for me to wait you&rsquo;re famous enough as a superheroine.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I don&rsquo;t even intend to become famous!&rdquo;
&ldquo;Do you really think you can keep a low profile? How many people have seen you use super powers yet? You of all people should know how the media are going to react once word of a real life superheroine reaches them.&rdquo;
&ldquo;You have been seen as well, Fred even got a clearer view on you than anybody who saw me! You could just as well be the heroine and I the sidekick!&rdquo;
&ldquo;Not when you consider what you&rsquo;ve done so far compared to me. You went around saving people while my only action comes across as bullying at best. Even if Fred doesn&rsquo;t go around badmouthing me, you already have the better reputation to become the hero.&rdquo;
&ldquo;As I said, I&rsquo;m not in it for the reputation or to be called a hero. I just want to help people and that&rsquo;s all.&rdquo;
&ldquo;My point exactly.&rdquo; Amanda sported a big smile as she said that. &ldquo;You are aware that you sounded like the big blue boy-scout himself just now?&rdquo;
&ldquo;The who?&rdquo;
&ldquo;I take that as a no. That just settles that you&rsquo;re the optimal choice for being the hero.&rdquo;
Michelle wanted to retort something, but instead, she let her head drop. Amanda had seemingly given it more than just a fleeting thought, so Michelle wouldn&rsquo;t be able to win this argument.
&ldquo;Do I really have to go public?&rdquo; she asked. &ldquo;You know I&rsquo;m not good when it comes to being in the spotlight.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I&rsquo;m not asking you to go public right now. Actually it would be stupid to do so. Eventually people will start asking about the new superheroine in town, and that will be your cue. And don&rsquo;t be concerned about your shyness. You literally stood naked in front of a crowd of clothed people and pulled it off really well.&rdquo;
Michelle&rsquo;s face turned red as she remembered the incident with the burning house. She had been utterly terrified when she found out she was naked but once her strange costume powers had taken care of that, all had worked out. It had felt great to be cheered on by these people. She could get used to that. Damn, she even had used this as an argument in her strange dream last night.
&ldquo;You win,&rdquo; Michelle exclaimed faintly. &ldquo;But as the sidekick you have to be my moral support.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Tch, please,&rdquo; Amanda snorted. &ldquo;This isn&rsquo;t the job of the sidekick. It&rsquo;s the job of the best friend!&rdquo;
Amanda walked over to a bunch of rocks that were lying on the floor. She picked one up - it was only a bit bigger than a basketball - and held it in one hand. Michelle spotted that her best friend seemed to struggle a bit with her balance. While she was definitely strong enough to lift it, her body wasn&rsquo;t heavy enough for her hold the boulder as she pleased. After a few seconds of testing, Amanda threw the rock in Michelle&rsquo;s direction. But what was supposed to be a basketball pass with a rock in place of a ball looked unintended funny as Amanda hadn&rsquo;t accounted for the recoil her own throw would cause. The rock missed Michelle by several feet while Amanda fell backwards and had to use her flight powers in order not to fall over. This gave Michelle an idea.
Picking the &lsquo;ball&rsquo; back up, Michelle also took her time to get accustomed to its weight. Then she used her own flight powers to steady herself while throwing the rock to Amanda. Her friend had paid attention, though and was able to catch the rock almost perfectly. The process repeated several times, with the rock being thrown faster and faster, then replaced with a bigger rock. After about half an hour, the two superwomen decided to stop this little game. Not because playing ball with rocks that could easily kill everybody due to size and speed of the projectiles wasn&rsquo;t fun, but the super energy they consumed was pretty high. Interestingly, they used up more energy for their flight powers than for the super strength.
As their energy began to fade, they decided it would be better to return home instead of risking an early transformation back to normal right in the middle of nowhere. Arriving at her apartment, Michelle wanted to use the opportunity to refill the vials she had given Amanda yesterday, but her best friend was adamant that one dose would be all she needed for now. While she would have preferred to have Amanda transform as many times as herself, Michelle accepted her best friends’ decision. She wouldn&rsquo;t have had any chance in an argument either, as Michelle didn&rsquo;t even know for sure why she wanted Amanda to transform more often - or at all for that matter. Still, Michelle knew that when it came to it, Amanda would support her in any possible way. Once her redheaded friend had left to return to her own apartment, Michelle began to think of all the troublesome things the future might hold for them. She couldn&rsquo;t really describe it, but for some reason - maybe it was the trust and support from her best friend - instead of being terrified, she couldn&rsquo;t wait for tomorrow.
